<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07836</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROMOTING SOCIO-ECONOMIC ACTIVITY AND REGIONAL CONNECTIVITY BY RATIONALIZING THE LOCAL ROAD NETWORK SYSTEM</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Recognizes the importance of investing in local roads and directs attention to the critical role of local government units (LGUs) in rationalizing the local road network; Provides for a weighing system that shall identify a more streamlined classification of local roads, transferring the jurisdiction of low priority roads to municipalities and high priority ones to the provincial level.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-05-31</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC WORKS AND HIGHWAYS ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>